hh3cPsePortTable.name: hh3cPsePortTable
hh3cPsePortTable.description: The indexing scheme is taken form that used by the IETF Power MIB. The same indexing scheme is used to give continuity in behaviour between that standard and this extensions definitioin.

hh3cPsePortEntry.name: hh3cPsePortEntry
hh3cPsePortEntry.description: The pethPsePortGroupIndex is imported from the IETF Power MIB and uniquely identifies the group containing the port to which power ethernet PSE is connected. Group means (box in the stack, module in a rack). The pethPsePortPowerIndex is imported from the IETF Power MIB and uniquely identifies the power ethernet PSE port within group pethPseGroupIndex to which the power Ethernet PSE entry is connected. This value will match the local port number on a switch.

hh3cPsePortFaultDescription.name: hh3cPsePortFaultDescription
hh3cPsePortFaultDescription.description: The object supports the fault category of the IETF Power MIB [1] pethPsePortDetectionStatus object. A textual description containing more information about the nature of this fault is provided by this object. Typically this will detail the precise PoE hardware state which is causing the pethPsePortDetectionStatus object to be in the 'fault' state. It is a DisplayString of up to 255 characters.

hh3cPsePortPeakPower.name: hh3cPsePortPeakPower
hh3cPsePortPeakPower.description: The object specifies the peak power which has been consumed by the port. It is defined as the highest measured value of power in milliWatts that has been consumed by the port. Its value is only reset when link is lost, the port is PoE disabled or when it is manually reset by the user asspecified below. It is a read/write integer value with units of milliWatts. Writing a value of zero to this object resets its value to zero. Writing any other value to this object has no effect on its value and an error is returned.

hh3cPsePortAveragePower.name: hh3cPsePortAveragePower
hh3cPsePortAveragePower.description: The object specifies the average power which has been consumed by the port. This object is a read/write integer value with units of milliWatts. Writing a value of zero to this object resets its value to zero. Writing any other value to this object has no effect on its value and an error is returned.

hh3cPsePortCurrentPower.name: hh3cPsePortCurrentPower
hh3cPsePortCurrentPower.description: The object specifies the power currently being consumed by the port. It is a read only integer value with units of milliWatts.

hh3cPsePortPowerLimit.name: hh3cPsePortPowerLimit
hh3cPsePortPowerLimit.description: The object specifies the power limit set for this port. The PSE will not supply more than this level of power to the specified port. It is a read/write integer value with units of milliWatts.

hh3cPsePortProfileIndex.name: hh3cPsePortProfileIndex
hh3cPsePortProfileIndex.description: Indicates the power profile which is currently associated with this port. This object references the corresponding hh3cPseProfileIndex object in the power profiles table. A value of zero is a special case and indicates that no power profile is currently associated with this port. When hh3cPseProfileIndex is set to an index of existent profile, pethPsePortPowerPairs, pethPsePortPowerPriority, pethPsePortAdminEnable and hh3cPsePortPowerLimit will be set to the same as corresponding value. PethPsePortPowerPairs, pethPsePortPowerPriority and pethPsePortAdminEnable are objects of rfc3621-Power-Ethernet.mib.

hh3cMainPseEntry.name: hh3cMainPseEntry
hh3cMainPseEntry.description: The pethMainPseGroupIndex is imported from the IETF Power MIB and uniquely identifies the group containing the port to which power ethernet PSE is connected. Group means (box in the stack, module in a rack) and the value 1 MUST be used for non-modular devices.

hh3cMainPsePowerLimit.name: hh3cMainPsePowerLimit
hh3cMainPsePowerLimit.description: The object specifies the power limit set for the unit as a whole. The PoE unit will already have a nominal power defined by the IETF Power MIB [1] pethMainPsePower object. This OPTIONAL object specifies a further limit to this nominal power value. This may be useful to control the thermals of the unit, or for internal testing purposes. One possible use for this object may be to lower the power consumption of the unit if one or more of the internal fans have broken. It is a read/write integer value with units of Watts (note - Watts is chosen instead of milliWatts here since the IETF Power MIB [1] measures unit based parameters, such as the pethMainPsePower object, in units of Watts).

hh3cMainPseAveragePower.name: hh3cMainPseAveragePower
hh3cMainPseAveragePower.description: The object specifies the average power which has been consumed by the port. It is a read/write integer value with units of Watts (note - Watts is chosen instead of milliWatts here since the IETF Power MIB [1] measures unit based parameters, such as the pethMainPsePower object, in units of Watts). Writing a value of zero to this object resets its value to zero. Writing any other value to this object has no effect on its value and an error is returned.

hh3cMainPsePeakPower.name: hh3cMainPsePeakPower
hh3cMainPsePeakPower.description: The object specifies the peak power which has been consumed for PoE. It is defined as the highest measured value of power in milliWatts that has been consumed at any one point in time by the sum of the PoE ports. Its value is only reset when the unit is powered on or when it is manually reset by the user as specifiedbelow. It is a read/write integer value with units of Watts (note - Watts is chosen instead of milliWatts here since the IETF Power MIB [1] measures unit based parameters, such as the pethMainPsePower object, in units of Watts). Writing a value of zero to this object resets its value to zero. Writing any other value to this object has noeffect on its value and an error is returned.

hh3cMainGuaranteedPowerRemaining.name: hh3cMainGuaranteedPowerRemaining
hh3cMainGuaranteedPowerRemaining.description: The object specifies the amount of power remaining in the guaranteed power pool. Each time a port is placed into guaranteed mode it reserves a set amount of power out of the total guaranteed power pool for the system. This intention of this object is to give the client of this MIB (whether that be the CLI or the Web interface or the end user) an indication of how many ports can still be placed into guaranteed mode. It is a read only integer value with units of Watts(note - Watts is chosen instead of milliWatts here since the IETF Power MIB [1] measures unit based parameters,such as the pethMainPsePower object, in units of Watts).

hh3cMainPsePriorityMode.name: hh3cMainPsePriorityMode
hh3cMainPsePriorityMode.description: Describes or controls the priority mode on slot which must be enabled firstly. When a new board is inserted, and the power is over-load, a value of disconnection(0) means that the power will stop supply to the low priority slot ; A value of non-disconnection(1) means that the slot still supply when a new board is inserted, and the power is over-load too.

hh3cMainPseLegacy.name: hh3cMainPseLegacy
hh3cMainPseLegacy.description: Describes or controls the legacy mode on slot which must be enabled firstly. Legacy mode: standard or nonstandard PD detection mode.

hh3cMainPsePowerPriority.name: hh3cMainPsePowerPriority
hh3cMainPsePowerPriority.description: Describes or controls the priority of the PSE. The priority will be used by the PSE policy to prevent from power overloading. If the priority of PSE is set to critical, the PSE will turn into guaranteed mode. The priority could be used by a control mechanism that prevents power overloading by disconnecting PSEs with lower power priority. PSEs that connect devices critical to the application should be set to higher priority.

hh3cPseProfilesTable.name: hh3cPseProfilesTable
hh3cPseProfilesTable.description: A table of objects representing a set of power profiles. Power profiles can be applied to PoE ports, which have the effect of automatically setting the priority, power limit and PoE enable MIB objects to the values specified in the power profile.

hh3cPseProfilesEntry.name: hh3cPseProfilesEntry
hh3cPseProfilesEntry.description: A set of objects that display and control the Main power of a PSE.

hh3cPseProfileIndex.name: hh3cPseProfileIndex
hh3cPseProfileIndex.description: The index of the profile. This uniquely allow the profile to be identified.

hh3cPseProfileName.name: hh3cPseProfileName
hh3cPseProfileName.description: Assigns the profile a name with which the settings can be assiciated with. For example, 'NBX Phone'.

hh3cPseProfilePowerMode.name: hh3cPseProfilePowerMode
hh3cPseProfilePowerMode.description: The power mode associated with this power profile. There are two possible power modes as follows: powerDisabled, powerEnabled. When a power profile is applied to a PSE port, this value dictates the settings of the ports pethPsePortPowerPriority and pethPsePortAdminEnable objects.

hh3cPseProfilePowerLimit.name: hh3cPseProfilePowerLimit
hh3cPseProfilePowerLimit.description: The power limit to be applied to the ports hh3cPsePortPowerLimit object when the profile is applied to the PSE port. Expressed in milliWatts.

hh3cPseProfilePriority.name: hh3cPseProfilePriority
hh3cPseProfilePriority.description: This object controls the priority of the port from the point of view of a power management algorithm. The priority that is set by this variable could be used by a control mechanism that prevents over current situations by disconnecting first ports with lower power priority. Ports that connect devices critical to the operation of the network - like the E911 telephones ports - should be set to higher priority.

hh3cPseProfilePairs.name: hh3cPseProfilePairs
hh3cPseProfilePairs.description: Describes or controls the pairs in use. If the value of pethPsePortPowerPairsControl is true, this object is writable. A value of signal(1) means that the signal pairs only are in use. A value of spare(2) means that the spare pairs only are in use.

hh3cPseProfileApplyNum.name: hh3cPseProfileApplyNum
hh3cPseProfileApplyNum.description: The number of this profile which has been applied. If hh3cPseProfileApplyNum is not zero, user can't change the current line.

hh3cPseProfileRowStatus.name: hh3cPseProfileRowStatus
hh3cPseProfileRowStatus.description: The status of this classifier. If hh3cPseProfileApplyNum is not zero, user can't delete the current line.

hh3cPseAutoDetectActive.name: hh3cPseAutoDetectActive
hh3cPseAutoDetectActive.description: The object specifies whether the device auto-detection feature is active. If this object is set to Active, and a known powered device is detected, then the port will automatically switch to Auto-Guaranteed mode. This is a stackwide object (ie. it is not referenced by group index).

hh3cPsePowerMaxValue.name: hh3cPsePowerMaxValue
hh3cPsePowerMaxValue.description: The object specifies the max poe power for lanswitch. The value should between the power currently and the max power.

hh3cPsePolicyMode.name: hh3cPsePolicyMode
hh3cPsePolicyMode.description: The PSE policy only applies to the situation that when a new board (PSE) is inserted, and the power is overload. A value of priority(2) means that the power will stop supplying to the low priority PSE. About PSE priority, please refer to hh3cMainPsePowerPriority. A value of disabled(1) means that the power will stop supplying to the new inserted PSE. The default value of this object is disabled(1).

hh3cPDPolicyMode.name: hh3cPDPolicyMode
hh3cPDPolicyMode.description: The PD policy only applies to the situation that when a new PD is inserted, and the power of PSE is overload. A value of priority(2) means that the power will stop supplying to the low priority port PD. About port priority, please refer to pethPsePortPowerPriority. A value of disabled(1) means that the slot stop supplying to the new inserted PD. The default value of this object is disabled(1).

hh3cpsePDChangeNotification.name: hh3cpsePDChangeNotification
hh3cpsePDChangeNotification.description: This notification indicates if PD has been inserted or pulled out.

hh3cPOEDisconnectNotification.name: hh3cPOEDisconnectNotification
hh3cPOEDisconnectNotification.description: This notification indicates the POE power module does not disconnect.

hh3cPOEInputErrorNotification.name: hh3cPOEInputErrorNotification
hh3cPOEInputErrorNotification.description: This notification indicates the POE power module input error.

hh3cPOEOutputErrorNotification.name: hh3cPOEOutputErrorNotification
hh3cPOEOutputErrorNotification.description: This notification indicates the POE power module output error.

hh3cPOEOverVoltageNotification.name: hh3cPOEOverVoltageNotification
hh3cPOEOverVoltageNotification.description: This notification indicates the POE power module overruns the voltage limit.

hh3cPOEOverTempNotification.name: hh3cPOEOverTempNotification
hh3cPOEOverTempNotification.description: This notification indicates the POE power module overruns the temperature limit.

hh3cPOEFanErrorNotification.name: hh3cPOEFanErrorNotification
hh3cPOEFanErrorNotification.description: This notification indicates the POE power module fan error.

hh3cPOEModuleShutdownNotification.name: hh3cPOEModuleShutdownNotification
hh3cPOEModuleShutdownNotification.description: This notification indicates the POE power module is closed.

hh3cPOECurRestrictedNotification.name: hh3cPOECurRestrictedNotification
hh3cPOECurRestrictedNotification.description: This notification indicates the POE power module current is restricted.

hh3cPOEACSwitchNotification.name: hh3cPOEACSwitchNotification
hh3cPOEACSwitchNotification.description: This notification indicates the AC input switch alarm of this POE power.

hh3cPOEACInCurANotification.name: hh3cPOEACInCurANotification
hh3cPOEACInCurANotification.description: This notification indicates the AC input current A alarm state of this POE power.

hh3cPOEACInCurBNotification.name: hh3cPOEACInCurBNotification
hh3cPOEACInCurBNotification.description: This notification indicates the AC input current B alarm state of this POE power.

hh3cPOEACInCurCNotification.name: hh3cPOEACInCurCNotification
hh3cPOEACInCurCNotification.description: This notification indicates the AC input current C alarm state of this POE power.

hh3cPOEACSwitchVolABNotification.name: hh3cPOEACSwitchVolABNotification
hh3cPOEACSwitchVolABNotification.description: This notification indicates the AC input voltage AB alarm state of this POE power.

hh3cPOEACSwitchVolBCNotification.name: hh3cPOEACSwitchVolBCNotification
hh3cPOEACSwitchVolBCNotification.description: This notification indicates the AC input voltage BC alarm state of this POE power.

hh3cPOEACSwitchVolCANotification.name: hh3cPOEACSwitchVolCANotification
hh3cPOEACSwitchVolCANotification.description: This notification indicates the AC input voltage CA alarm state of this POE power.

hh3cPOEDCOutVolNotification.name: hh3cPOEDCOutVolNotification
hh3cPOEDCOutVolNotification.description: This notification indicates the DC output alarm of this POE power.

hh3cPOEShutdownNotification.name: hh3cPOEShutdownNotification
hh3cPOEShutdownNotification.description: This notification indicates the whole POE power has been shutdown.

hh3cPsePortGroup.name: hh3cPsePortGroup
hh3cPsePortGroup.description: A collection of objects should be supported at the same time.

hh3cMainPseGroup.name: hh3cMainPseGroup
hh3cMainPseGroup.description: A collection of objects should be supported at the same time.

hh3cPseScalarGroup.name: hh3cPseScalarGroup
hh3cPseScalarGroup.description: A collection of scalar objects supported.

hh3cPseProfilesGroup.name: hh3cPseProfilesGroup
hh3cPseProfilesGroup.description: A collection of objects should be supported at the same time.

hh3cPOEPowerDCOutStateGroup.name: hh3cPOEPowerDCOutStateGroup
hh3cPOEPowerDCOutStateGroup.description: The DC out power state group.

hh3cPOEPowerDCOutInfoGroup.name: hh3cPOEPowerDCOutInfoGroup
hh3cPOEPowerDCOutInfoGroup.description: The power AC input switch information group

hh3cPOEThresholdACMimimum.name: hh3cPOEThresholdACMimimum
hh3cPOEThresholdACMimimum.description: Input threshold AC minimum. It is a read-write node. The value of this node is 'OCTET STRING', it is used to describe a float value. So this string should fit the following rule: 1. This string should be terminated by '\0'; 2. Every characters should be number or radix point; 3. The radix point should occur only once, and it should not be the first or the last character of the string. The value of this node should be smaller than 264.0V and larger than 90.0V. And it should be smaller than the hh3cPOEThresholdACMaximum.

hh3cPOEThresholdACMaximum.name: hh3cPOEThresholdACMaximum
hh3cPOEThresholdACMaximum.description: Input threshold AC maximum. It is a read-write node. The value of this node is 'OCTET STRING', it is used to describe a float value. So this string should fit the following rule: 1. This string should be terminated by '\0'; 2. Every characters should be number or radix point; 3. The radix point should occur only once, and it should not be the first or the last character of the string. It should be smaller than 264.0V and larger than 90.0V. And it should be larger than the hh3cPOEThresholdACMinimum.

hh3cPOEThresholdDCMinimum.name: hh3cPOEThresholdDCMinimum
hh3cPOEThresholdDCMinimum.description: Input threshold DC minimum. It is a read-write node. The value of this node is 'OCTET STRING', it is used to describe a float value. So this string should fit the following rule: 1. This string should be terminated by '\0'; 2. Every characters should be number or radix point; 3. The radix point should occur only once, and it should not be the first or the last character of the string. It should be smaller than 47.0V and larger than 45.0V.

hh3cPOEThresholdDCMaximum.name: hh3cPOEThresholdDCMaximum
hh3cPOEThresholdDCMaximum.description: Input threshold DC maximum. It is a read-write node. The value of this node is 'OCTET STRING', it is used to describe a float value. So this string should fit the following rule: 1. This string should be terminated by '\0'; 2. Every characters should be number or radix point; 3. The radix point should occur only once, and it should not be the first or the last character of the string. It should be smaller than 57.0V and larger than 55.0V.

hh3cPOEPowerModuleNum.name: hh3cPOEPowerModuleNum
hh3cPOEPowerModuleNum.description: The number of the power modules.

hh3cPOESupervisionModuleName.name: hh3cPOESupervisionModuleName
hh3cPOESupervisionModuleName.description: The object specifies the Supervision Module name on this POE power.

hh3cPOESMMajorVersion.name: hh3cPOESMMajorVersion
hh3cPOESMMajorVersion.description: The object specifies the high byte of the monitor module version.

hh3cPOESMMinorVersion.name: hh3cPOESMMinorVersion
hh3cPOESMMinorVersion.description: The object specifies the low byte of the monitor module version.

hh3cPOESMFactorName.name: hh3cPOESMFactorName
hh3cPOESMFactorName.description: The object specifies the name of the manufactor.

hh3cPOEModuleInfoTable.name: hh3cPOEModuleInfoTable
hh3cPOEModuleInfoTable.description: The table of the module information on this POE power.

hh3cPOEModuleInfoEntry.name: hh3cPOEModuleInfoEntry
hh3cPOEModuleInfoEntry.description: The entry of the module information on this POE power.

hh3cPOEModuleIndex.name: hh3cPOEModuleIndex
hh3cPOEModuleIndex.description: The index of the current module on this POE power. It is also the index of hh3cPOEModuleInfoTable. The range of this node is from 1 to hh3cPOEPowerModuleNum.

hh3cPOEModuleID.name: hh3cPOEModuleID
hh3cPOEModuleID.description: The ID of the current module on this POE power.

hh3cPOEModuleInfoPower.name: hh3cPOEModuleInfoPower
hh3cPOEModuleInfoPower.description: The power of the current module on this POE power.

hh3cPOEModuleHardVerInfo.name: hh3cPOEModuleHardVerInfo
hh3cPOEModuleHardVerInfo.description: The hardware version information of the current module on this POE power.

hh3cPOEDCOutStateModuleNum.name: hh3cPOEDCOutStateModuleNum
hh3cPOEDCOutStateModuleNum.description: The module number on this POE power. It is the maximum of the hh3cPOEDCOutStateIndex.

hh3cPOEDCOutStateTable.name: hh3cPOEDCOutStateTable
hh3cPOEDCOutStateTable.description: The table of DC output power state on this POE power.

hh3cPOEDCOutStateEntry.name: hh3cPOEDCOutStateEntry
hh3cPOEDCOutStateEntry.description: The entry of the DC output power state on this POE power.

hh3cPOEDCOutStateIndex.name: hh3cPOEDCOutStateIndex
hh3cPOEDCOutStateIndex.description: The index of the DC output power state on this POE power. The range of this node is from 1 to hh3cPOEDCOutStateModuleNum.

hh3cPOEDCOutDCVolAlarm.name: hh3cPOEDCOutDCVolAlarm
hh3cPOEDCOutDCVolAlarm.description: The DC output alarm of the DC output power state on this POE power. The value of this node will be the following values: normal (1), underLimit (2), aboveLimit (3), fuseBroken (4), switchOff (5), otherError (6).

hh3cPOEDCOutCurNum.name: hh3cPOEDCOutCurNum
hh3cPOEDCOutCurNum.description: The number of DC output current on this POE power. It is the maximum of hh3cPOEDCOutInfoIndex.

hh3cPOEDCOutInfoTable.name: hh3cPOEDCOutInfoTable
hh3cPOEDCOutInfoTable.description: The table of the DC output information on this POE power.

hh3cPOEDCOutInfoEntry.name: hh3cPOEDCOutInfoEntry
hh3cPOEDCOutInfoEntry.description: The entry of the DC output information on this POE power.

hh3cPOEDCOutInfoIndex.name: hh3cPOEDCOutInfoIndex
hh3cPOEDCOutInfoIndex.description: The index of the DC output information on this POE POWER. The range of this node is from 1 to hh3cPOEDCOutCurNum.

hh3cPOEDCOutVol.name: hh3cPOEDCOutVol
hh3cPOEDCOutVol.description: The DC output voltage of the current DC output on this POE power.

hh3cPOEDCOutInfoLoadCur.name: hh3cPOEDCOutInfoLoadCur
hh3cPOEDCOutInfoLoadCur.description: The total load current of the current DC output on this POE power.

hh3cPOEACSwitchStateModuleNum.name: hh3cPOEACSwitchStateModuleNum
hh3cPOEACSwitchStateModuleNum.description: The number of the AC swtich state module on this POE power. It is the maximum of hh3cPOEACSwitchStateIndex.

hh3cPOEACSwitchStateTable.name: hh3cPOEACSwitchStateTable
hh3cPOEACSwitchStateTable.description: The table of the AC switch state on this POE power.

hh3cPOEACSwitchStateEntry.name: hh3cPOEACSwitchStateEntry
hh3cPOEACSwitchStateEntry.description: The entry of the AC switch state on this POE power.

hh3cPOEACSwitchStateIndex.name: hh3cPOEACSwitchStateIndex
hh3cPOEACSwitchStateIndex.description: The index of the AC switch state on this POE power. The range of this node is from 1 to hh3cPOEACSwitchStateModuleNum.

hh3cPOEACSwitchState.name: hh3cPOEACSwitchState
hh3cPOEACSwitchState.description: The AC switch state on this POE power. The value of this node will be one of the following values: on (1), off (2), highVoltInput (3), lowVoltInput (4)

hh3cPOEInCurStateModuleNum.name: hh3cPOEInCurStateModuleNum
hh3cPOEInCurStateModuleNum.description: The DC input current state of the module on this POE power. It is the maximum of the hh3cPOESwitchStateVolExIndex.

hh3cPOEInCurAState.name: hh3cPOEInCurAState
hh3cPOEInCurAState.description: The current A state in the DC input on this POE power. normal (1), underLimit (2), aboveLimit (3), lackPhrase (4), fuseBroken (5), switchOff (6), otherError (7).

hh3cPOEInCurBState.name: hh3cPOEInCurBState
hh3cPOEInCurBState.description: The current B state in the DC input on this POE power. The value of this node will be one of the following values: normal (1), underLimit (2), aboveLimit (3), lackPhrase (4), fuseBroken (5), switchOff (6), otherError (7).

hh3cPOEInCurCState.name: hh3cPOEInCurCState
hh3cPOEInCurCState.description: The current C state in the DC input on this POE power. The value of this node will be one of the following values: normal (1), underLimit (2), aboveLimit (3), lackPhrase (4), fuseBroken (5), switchOff (6), otherError (7).

hh3cPOESwitchStateVolExTable.name: hh3cPOESwitchStateVolExTable
hh3cPOESwitchStateVolExTable.description: All alarm status of the VOL status. The value of this node will be one of the following values: normal (1), underLimit (2), aboveLimit (3), lackPhrase (4), fuseBroken (5), switchOff (6), otherError (7).

hh3cPOESwitchStateVolExEntry.name: hh3cPOESwitchStateVolExEntry
hh3cPOESwitchStateVolExEntry.description: The hh3cPOESwitchStateVolExIndex will match the number of the VOL status.

hh3cPOESwitchStateVolExIndex.name: hh3cPOESwitchStateVolExIndex
hh3cPOESwitchStateVolExIndex.description: The object species the index of the VOL status. The range of this node is from 1 to hh3cPOEInCurStateModuleNum.

hh3cPOESwitchStateInVolAB.name: hh3cPOESwitchStateInVolAB
hh3cPOESwitchStateInVolAB.description: The object specifies the VOL AB alarm in each VOL status. The value of this node will be one of the following values: normal (1), underLimit (2), aboveLimit (3), lackPhrase (4), fuseBroken (5), switchOff (6), otherError (7).

hh3cPOESwitchStateInVolBC.name: hh3cPOESwitchStateInVolBC
hh3cPOESwitchStateInVolBC.description: The object specifies the VOL BC alarm in each VOL status. The value of this node will be one of the following values: normal (1), underLimit (2), aboveLimit (3), lackPhrase (4), fuseBroken (5), switchOff (6), otherError (7).

hh3cPOESwitchStateInVolCA.name: hh3cPOESwitchStateInVolCA
hh3cPOESwitchStateInVolCA.description: The object specifies the VOL CA alarm in each VOL status. The value of this node will be one of the following values: normal (1), underLimit (2), aboveLimit (3), lackPhrase (4), fuseBroken (5), switchOff (6), otherError (7).

hh3cPOEAlarmStateModuleNum.name: hh3cPOEAlarmStateModuleNum
hh3cPOEAlarmStateModuleNum.description: The object specifies the number of the power modules in alarm state.

hh3cPOEAlarmStateInfoTable.name: hh3cPOEAlarmStateInfoTable
hh3cPOEAlarmStateInfoTable.description: All alarm states in the POE power modules.

hh3cPOEAlarmStateInfoEntry.name: hh3cPOEAlarmStateInfoEntry
hh3cPOEAlarmStateInfoEntry.description: The hh3cPOEAlarmModuleInfoIndex will match the number of the power module.

hh3cPOEAlarmModuleInfoIndex.name: hh3cPOEAlarmModuleInfoIndex
hh3cPOEAlarmModuleInfoIndex.description: The index specifies the index of the Hh3cPOEAlarmStateInfoEntry table. The range of this node is from 1 to hh3cPOEAlarmStateModuleNum.

hh3cPOEModuleDisconnect.name: hh3cPOEModuleDisconnect
hh3cPOEModuleDisconnect.description: The node specifies the alarm state: The module does not link. The value of this node is one of the following values: normal (1), alarm (2).

hh3cPOEModuleInputError.name: hh3cPOEModuleInputError
hh3cPOEModuleInputError.description: The node specifies the alarm state: Input error. The value of this node is one of the following values: normal (1), alarm (2).

hh3cPOEModuleOutputError.name: hh3cPOEModuleOutputError
hh3cPOEModuleOutputError.description: The node specifies the alarm state: Output error. The value of this node is one of the following values: normal (1), alarm (2).
